  "texts": [
    "Therefore, we believe that a survey of deep learning in all software engineering subareas may be more beneficial for software engineering researchers.",
    "Second, deep learning belongs to representation learning, and deep learning techniques for software engineering are thus highly specific to different artifacts in software development.",
    "As different subareas of software engineering typically share some common artifacts, putting different subareas into one survey would help researchers from different subareas understand the strengths and weaknesses of different deep learning techniques.",
    "For example, a deep learning technique based on source code may impact all subareas related to the comprehension, generation, and modification of codes.One issue that raises in preparing this survey is that software engineering is a big discipline and the applications of deep learning techniques may thus touch some subareas in an uninfluential way.",
    "When facing such a subarea, where there are very few deep learning papers, we feel that these papers can hardly reflect the essence of deep learning research in that subarea."
  ],
